{
  "texts": [
    "A model's ability to predict the next merchant serves as a proxy for its performance in recommendation applications.",
    "To achieve the second objective, we trained two additional models employing alternative loss aggregation strategies: 1) simple summation of losses, and 2) weighting losses for equal contribution.",
    "The experiment results are presented in Table 1.",
    "Comparing the performance of TREASURE with the two singlepurpose models, we observe that our method simultaneously outperforms both.",
    "This indicates that the proposed foundation model not only conserves resources by enabling a single multi-purpose model to replace multiple single-purpose ones but also delivers superior prediction quality."
  ]
}